line_1: And this her sex can well attest,
line_2: With beauty she was never blest,

line_1: Ye, conscious Trees and Fountains, can attest
line_2: The pious Mother comes, with Grief oppress'd:

line_1: For sage experience shall this truth attest:
line_2: Ask hoary time, what nation is most blest?

line_1: Thee only, sober Goddess! I attest,
line_2: In smiles chastis'd, and decent graces drest.

line_1: He, the said SELIM, did attest,
line_2: In letter to one GILBERT WEST,

line_1: Long may such bliss, by such enjoy'd, attest,
line_2: The greatly virtuous are the greatly blest!

line_1: And frequent starts, and heart-drawn sighs attest,
line_2: Mark what convulsions heave his martyr'd breast,

line_1: And frequent starts, and heart-drawn sighs attest,
line_2: Though Nature grants him sleep, that Guilt denies him rest.
